cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new data structure for solving the approximate near-neighbor search problem.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses locality sensitive hashing (LSH) and compressed sensing techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the role of sparsity in compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility as near-neighbor search is a common problem in computer vision applications.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possibility as the paper mentions applications in high-speed data mining and internet-of-things (IoT), which are related to multimedia data processing.
